# JWT Secret (for internal session tokens)
JWT_SECRET=your-jwt-secret-change-in-production

# Auth0 Setup Instructions:
# 1. Create an Auth0 account at https://auth0.com
# 2. Create a new Application (Regular Web Application)
# 3. In Application settings:
#    - Allowed Callback URLs: http://localhost:3000/auth/callback, https://your-domain.com/auth/callback
#    - Allowed Logout URLs: http://localhost:3000, https://your-domain.com
#    - Allowed Web Origins: http://localhost:3000, https://your-domain.com
# 4. Enable Google social connection:
#    - Go to Authentication > Social
#    - Enable Google and configure with your Google OAuth credentials
#    - Or use Auth0's dev keys for testing
# 5. Copy Client ID, Client Secret, and Domain to this file

# Note: User data encryption uses a user-provided passphrase (never stored on server)
# No server-side encryption secret is needed
